<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Road to LA28 — Men's −68kg Campaign</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Oswald:wght@400;500;600;700&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@500;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root{
    --ink:#13171F; --ink-2:#1C222D; --paper:#EBEEF3; --panel:#FFFFFF;
    --chung:#1A5FD0; --chung-d:#103E8C; --hong:#D11F39; --hong-d:#9c1528;
    --gold:#C9A227; --gold-d:#9c7d18;
    --muted:#5C6573; --muted-2:#8a93a3; --line:#D6DCE5; --line-2:#E7EBF1;
    --ok:#1B8a5a; --warn:#C9701f;
    --disp:'Oswald',system-ui,sans-serif; --body:'Inter',system-ui,sans-serif; --mono:'JetBrains Mono',ui-monospace,monospace;
  }
  *{box-sizing:border-box}
  html{scroll-behavior:smooth}
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion:reduce){html{scroll-behavior:auto}}
  body{margin:0;background:var(--paper);color:var(--ink);font-family:var(--body);line-height:1.6;-webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased}
  h1,h2,h3,h4{font-family:var(--disp);font-weight:600;line-height:1.05;margin:0;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.01em}
  a{color:var(--chung-d);text-decoration:none}
  a:hover{text-decoration:underline}
  .mono{font-family:var(--mono)}

  /* ---------- HERO ---------- */
  .hero{position:relative;background:var(--ink);color:#fff;overflow:hidden;padding:64px 24px 56px}
  .hero .corner{position:absolute;width:46vw;height:46vw;max-width:520px;max-height:520px;border-radius:50%;filter:blur(8px);opacity:.5}
  .hero .c-blue{background:radial-gradient(circle at 30% 30%,var(--chung),transparent 65%);top:-14%;left:-12%}
  .hero .c-red{background:radial-gradient(circle at 70% 70%,var(--hong),transparent 65%);bottom:-18%;right:-12%}
  .hero-inner{position:relative;max-width:1080px;margin:0 auto;z-index:2}
  .eyebrow{font-family:var(--disp);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.28em;font-size:13px;font-weight:500;color:var(--gold)}
  .hero h1{font-size:clamp(44px,9vw,108px);font-weight:700;margin:14px 0 6px;letter-spacing:.005em}
  .hero h1 .blue{color:#6ea8ff}.hero h1 .red{color:#ff6f82}
  .hero .sub{font-size:clamp(17px,2.4vw,22px);max-width:680px;color:#c7cedb;font-weight:400}
  .scoreboard{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:14px;margin-top:34px}
  .sb{background:rgba(255,255,255,.06);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,.12);border-radius:10px;padding:14px 18px;min-width:120px}
  .sb .n{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:30px;font-weight:700;color:#fff;line-height:1}
  .sb .l{font-size:11.5px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.12em;color:var(--muted-2);margin-top:8px;font-weight:600}
  .verdict{margin-top:34px;border-left:3px solid var(--gold);padding:12px 0 12px 20px;max-width:760px;color:#dde3ec;font-size:15.5px}
  .verdict b{color:#fff}

  /* ---------- LAYOUT ---------- */
  .shell{max-width:1180px;margin:0 auto;display:grid;grid-template-columns:236px 1fr;gap:0}
  nav.toc{position:sticky;top:0;align-self:start;height:100vh;overflow-y:auto;padding:26px 18px 40px;border-right:1px solid var(--line);background:var(--paper)}
  nav.toc .brand{font-family:var(--disp);font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;font-size:15px;letter-spacing:.04em;color:var(--ink);line-height:1.1;margin-bottom:4px}
  nav.toc .brand small{display:block;font-family:var(--body);font-weight:600;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.14em;color:var(--hong);margin-top:6px}
  nav.toc ol{list-style:none;margin:18px 0 0;padding:0;counter-reset:s}
  nav.toc li{counter-increment:s}
  nav.toc a{display:flex;gap:9px;padding:6px 8px;border-radius:7px;color:var(--muted);font-size:13px;font-weight:500;line-height:1.25}
  nav.toc a::before{content:counter(s,decimal-leading-zero);font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;color:var(--muted-2);padding-top:1px}
  nav.toc a:hover{background:var(--line-2);text-decoration:none;color:var(--ink)}
  nav.toc a.active{background:var(--ink);color:#fff}
  nav.toc a.active::before{color:var(--gold)}
  main{padding:0 0 80px;min-width:0}
  .navbtn{display:none}

  section.block{padding:52px 40px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);scroll-margin-top:10px}
  section.block:nth-child(even){background:#e4e8ef}
  .sec-head{display:flex;align-items:baseline;gap:14px;margin-bottom:8px}
  .sec-num{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:14px;color:var(--hong);font-weight:700}
  h2.sec-title{font-size:clamp(26px,4vw,40px);font-weight:700}
  .lede{font-size:17px;color:var(--ink-2);max-width:760px;margin:14px 0 26px}
  .lede.tight{margin-bottom:14px}
  p{margin:0 0 14px;max-width:820px}
  .small{font-size:13.5px;color:var(--muted)}
  strong{font-weight:700}

  /* cards / grids */
  .grid{display:grid;gap:16px}
  .g2{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}.g3{grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr)}
  .card{background:var(--panel);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:20px}
  .card h3{font-size:18px;margin-bottom:6px;text-transform:none;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0}
  .card .k{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.04em;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase}
  .tag{display:inline-block;font-family:var(--disp);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.08em;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;padding:3px 9px;border-radius:20px;margin-bottom:10px}
  .t-real{background:#e7f4ee;color:var(--ok);border:1px solid #b8e0cd}
  .t-stretch{background:#fdeef0;color:var(--hong-d);border:1px solid #f3c7cf}
  .t-back{background:#eef2fb;color:var(--chung-d);border:1px solid #cdd9f3}
  .t-na{background:#eef0f3;color:var(--muted);border:1px solid var(--line)}
  .t-gold{background:#fbf3d8;color:var(--gold-d);border:1px solid #ecd99a}

  ul.clean{margin:0 0 14px;padding-left:0;list-style:none}
  ul.clean li{position:relative;padding:7px 0 7px 26px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line-2);max-width:840px}
  ul.clean li:last-child{border-bottom:0}
  ul.clean li::before{content:"";position:absolute;left:4px;top:15px;width:8px;height:8px;background:var(--chung);border-radius:2px;transform:rotate(45deg)}
  ul.clean li.red::before{background:var(--hong)}
  ul.clean li.gold::before{background:var(--gold)}

  table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:14px;background:var(--panel);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:10px;overflow:hidden;margin:6px 0 18px}
  .tbl-wrap{overflow-x:auto;-webkit-overflow-scrolling:touch}
  th,td{padding:10px 12px;text-align:left;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line-2)}
  th{background:var(--ink);color:#fff;font-family:var(--disp);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.06em;font-size:12.5px;font-weight:500;white-space:nowrap}
  td.mono,th.mono{font-family:var(--mono)}
  tbody tr:last-child td{border-bottom:0}
  tbody tr:hover{background:#f5f7fb}
  .hl{background:#fbf3d8 !important}
  .big{font-family:var(--mono);font-weight:700;color:var(--hong-d)}

  .callout{border:1px solid var(--line);border-left:4px solid var(--gold);background:var(--panel);border-radius:8px;padding:16px 18px;margin:18px 0;max-width:840px}
  .callout.blue{border-left-color:var(--chung)}
  .callout.red{border-left-color:var(--hong)}
  .callout .k{font-family:var(--disp);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.08em;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:var(--muted);margin-bottom:4px}

  /* loophole list */
  .loot{counter-reset:lp}
  .loot .row{display:flex;gap:16px;padding:16px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
  .loot .row:last-child{border-bottom:0}
  .loot .row::before{counter-increment:lp;content:counter(lp,decimal-leading-zero);font-family:var(--mono);font-weight:700;color:var(--gold-d);font-size:14px;padding-top:3px;min-width:26px}
  .loot h4{font-size:16px;text-transform:none;letter-spacing:0;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:3px}
  .loot p{margin:0;font-size:14.5px;color:var(--ink-2)}

  /* timeline */
  .rail{position:relative;margin:10px 0 0;padding-left:30px}
  .rail::before{content:"";position:absolute;left:8px;top:6px;bottom:6px;width:3px;background:linear-gradient(var(--chung),var(--hong))}
  .yr{font-family:var(--disp);font-weight:700;font-size:22px;margin:26px 0 8px;color:var(--ink)}
  .yr:first-child{margin-top:6px}
  .ev{position:relative;padding:10px 0 10px 4px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line-2);max-width:840px}
  .ev::before{content:"";position:absolute;left:-29px;top:16px;width:13px;height:13px;border-radius:50%;background:#fff;border:3px solid var(--chung)}
  .ev.key::before{border-color:var(--hong);background:var(--hong)}
  .ev.win::before{border-color:var(--gold);background:var(--gold)}
  .ev .d{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12px;font-weight:700;color:var(--hong-d);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.03em}
  .ev .w{font-weight:600}
  .ev .why{font-size:13.5px;color:var(--muted)}

  /* decision tree */
  .tree{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:13px;background:var(--ink);color:#dfe5ef;border-radius:12px;padding:22px;overflow-x:auto;line-height:1.9}
  .tree b{color:#fff}.tree .g{color:var(--gold)}.tree .bl{color:#6ea8ff}.tree .rd{color:#ff8593}

  .checklist{max-width:870px}
  .cl-group{margin:0 0 24px}
  .cl-group h3{font-size:14px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.07em;color:var(--hong-d);font-family:var(--disp);font-weight:600;margin:0 0 6px;padding-bottom:7px;border-bottom:2px solid var(--line)}
  label.check{display:flex;gap:13px;align-items:flex-start;padding:9px 2px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line-2);cursor:pointer}
  .cl-group label.check:last-child{border-bottom:0}
  label.check input{appearance:none;-webkit-appearance:none;min-width:20px;height:20px;margin:2px 0 0;border:2px solid var(--muted-2);border-radius:5px;cursor:pointer;position:relative;background:#fff}
  label.check input:checked{background:var(--chung);border-color:var(--chung)}
  label.check input:checked::after{content:"✓";position:absolute;inset:-2px 0 0 0;color:#fff;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center}
  label.check input:focus-visible{outline:2px solid var(--gold);outline-offset:2px}
  label.check span{font-size:14.5px;color:var(--ink-2)}
  label.check input:checked ~ span{color:var(--muted-2);text-decoration:line-through}
  label.check .g{font-family:var(--mono);font-weight:700;color:var(--hong-d);font-size:12.5px}
  footer{background:var(--ink);color:#aeb6c4;padding:34px 40px;font-size:13px}
  footer .eyebrow{color:var(--gold)}
  footer p{max-width:900px;color:#aeb6c4}

  .reveal{opacity:0;transform:translateY(14px);transition:opacity .5s ease,transform .5s ease}
  .reveal.in{opacity:1;transform:none}
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion:reduce){.reveal{opacity:1;transform:none;transition:none}}

  @media (max-width:900px){
    .shell{grid-template-columns:1fr}
    nav.toc{position:fixed;inset:0 0 0 auto;width:260px;height:100vh;z-index:50;transform:translateX(100%);transition:transform .25s ease;border-left:1px solid var(--line);border-right:0;box-shadow:-10px 0 30px rgba(0,0,0,.18)}
    nav.toc.open{transform:none}
    .navbtn{display:flex;position:fixed;top:14px;right:14px;z-index:60;background:var(--ink);color:#fff;border:0;border-radius:8px;font-family:var(--disp);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.08em;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;padding:10px 14px;cursor:pointer;align-items:center;gap:8px}
    section.block{padding:40px 22px}
    .g2,.g3{grid-template-columns:1fr}
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<button class="navbtn" id="navbtn" aria-label="Open contents">Contents ▾</button>

<header class="hero">
  <div class="corner c-blue"></div><div class="corner c-red"></div>
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="eyebrow">Team USA · Road to Los Angeles 2028</div>
    <h1>One seat.<br><span class="blue">−68</span> <span class="red">kg</span>.</h1>
    <p class="sub">128 fighters. 8 weight classes. Exactly one American man can stand on the −68kg mat in LA. This is the complete map of every way to make him that man — every route, every rule, every edge.</p>
    <div class="scoreboard">
      <div class="sb"><div class="n">1</div><div class="l">USA man at −68kg</div></div>
      <div class="sb"><div class="n">5</div><div class="l">Routes in</div></div>
      <div class="sb"><div class="n">40</div><div class="l">Point cap on opens / yr</div></div>
      <div class="sb"><div class="n">2027</div><div class="l">The decisive season</div></div>
      <div class="sb"><div class="n">2026</div><div class="l">Where it starts</div></div>
    </div>
    <div class="verdict">
      <b>The honest read:</b> finishing top-5 in the world in one senior season is a long shot in a division this deep. His most realistic door is the <b>host-country quota</b> — and the work that opens it is the <em>same</em> work that chases the ranking. So he runs one campaign and keeps every door open at once.
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<div class="shell">
  <nav class="toc" id="toc">
    <div class="brand">Road to LA28<small>MEN'S −68KG · DOSSIER</small></div>
    <ol>
      <li><a href="#fighter">The fighter &amp; the target</a></li>
      <li><a href="#routes">The 5 routes in</a></li>
      <li><a href="#scoreboards">The two scoreboards</a></li>
      <li><a href="#engine">The points engine</a></li>
      <li><a href="#edges">Every edge &amp; loophole</a></li>
      <li><a href="#opt1">Route 1 · World ranking</a></li>
      <li><a href="#opt3">Route 2 · Host quota</a></li>
      <li><a href="#opt4">Route 3 · Reallocation</a></li>
      <li><a href="#opt2">Route 4 · Grand Slam</a></li>
      <li><a href="#div">The −63 / −68 play</a></li>
      <li><a href="#gateway">The domestic gateway</a></li>
      <li><a href="#timeline">Master timeline</a></li>
      <li><a href="#tree">Decision tree</a></li>
      <li><a href="#risks">Traps to avoid</a></li>
      <li><a href="#act">Do this now</a></li>
      <li><a href="#checklist">Checklist</a></li>
    </ol>
  </nav>

  <main>

  <!-- 1 -->
  <section class="block reveal" id="fighter">
    <div class="sec-head"><span class="sec-num">01</span><h2 class="sec-title">The fighter &amp; the target</h2></div>
    <p class="lede tight">A seasoned junior (Cadet Worlds, Junior Worlds) turning 17 in January 2027 — which makes him a senior for all of 2027 and eligible for LA28.</p>
    <div class="grid g3">
      <div class="card"><div class="k" style="color:var(--chung)">Eligibility</div><h3>Cleared</h3><p class="small">Born on/before 31 Dec 2011, so he meets the LA28 age rule. Senior age is by year — he's senior-eligible the whole of 2027.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><div class="k" style="color:var(--hong)">Division</div><h3>−68kg Olympic</h3><p class="small">One of four men's Olympic classes. The USA may send only one man here, by any route.</p></div>
      <div class="card"><div class="k" style="color:var(--gold-d)">Host edge</div><h3>USA hosts</h3><p class="small">Opens a host quota and an Olympic 4-seed — but <em>closes</em> the Pan Am continental qualifier to him.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="callout"><div class="k">Paperwork (already handled — keep it live)</div>Kukkiwon Dan, WT Global Athlete License, U.S. passport valid 6 months past the Games, GMS registration, annual medical certificate, travel insurance, SafeSport &amp; anti-doping/whereabouts compliance. Any one lapsing ends the run, so treat them as standing maintenance.</div>
  </section>

  <!-- 2 -->
  <section class="block reveal" id="routes">
    <div class="sec-head"><span class="sec-num">02</span><h2 class="sec-title">The five routes in</h2></div>
    <p class="lede">Only one American man competes at −68kg. Here is every door to being that man, ranked by how realistic each is for a first-year senior.</p>
    <div class="grid g2">
      <div class="card"><span class="tag t-back">Backbone</span><h3>Host-country quota</h3><p class="small">USATKD picks 2 men's divisions for guaranteed host seats. Win the case that −68kg is one of them and he's the pick. His most realistic route. <a href="#opt3">→ Route 2</a></p></div>
      <div class="card"><span class="tag t-stretch">Stretch</span><h3>WT Olympic Ranking — top 5</h3><p class="small">Top 5 in the world at −68kg on the Jan 2028 ranking = automatic seat, no host spot used. Hard from a standing start, pursued anyway. <a href="#opt1">→ Route 1</a></p></div>
      <div class="card"><span class="tag t-real">Live safety net</span><h3>Reallocation</h3><p class="small">Finish 6th–20th and catch a seat when higher athletes or NOCs decline — including unused continental places. Rank high to qualify. <a href="#opt4">→ Route 3</a></p></div>
      <div class="card"><span class="tag t-stretch">Long shot</span><h3>Grand Slam Champions Series</h3><p class="small">Be #1 on Grand Slam merit points. Elite-entry only — a bonus if he wins big, not a plan. <a href="#opt2">→ Route 4</a></p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="callout red"><div class="k">Closed</div><strong>Continental (Pan Am) qualifier &amp; Universality places.</strong> The host nation can't enter its own continental qualifier, and Universality is for small-delegation nations. Neither is available — don't build around them. (But see the reallocation edge in §05.)</div>
  </section>

  <!-- 3 -->
  <section class="block reveal" id="scoreboards">
    <div class="sec-head"><span class="sec-num">03</span><h2 class="sec-title">The two scoreboards</h2></div>
    <p class="lede">He's playing for two things at once — and the beauty is that the same results move both.</p>
    <div class="grid g2">
      <div class="card" style="border-top:4px solid var(--chung)"><h3>A · The ranking number</h3><p class="small">His WT Olympic Ranking position. Top 5 wins a seat outright; a high number feeds the reallocation net. Decided by the <strong>January 2028</strong> ranking.</p></div>
      <div class="card" style="border-top:4px solid var(--hong)"><h3>B · The selection case</h3><p class="small">USATKD's host-quota decision, made by <strong>30 Sept 2027</strong>. Subjective, but they've published exactly what they weigh — medals at big events, recent form, wins over ranked names.</p></div>
    </div>
    <p>Pan Am medals, Grand Prix runs, quality wins — every one of them raises the ranking <em>and</em> strengthens the selection case. He never has to choose between the two; he runs a single campaign and both scoreboards climb together.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- 4 -->
  <section class="block reveal" id="engine">
    <div class="sec-head"><span class="sec-num">04</span><h2 class="sec-title">The points engine</h2></div>
    <p class="lede">How ranking points actually work — because the rules reward a handful of big events far more than a season of small ones.</p>

    <h3 style="font-size:18px;margin:18px 0 4px;text-transform:none;letter-spacing:0">Points by finish &amp; event grade</h3>
    <div class="tbl-wrap"><table>
      <thead><tr><th>Finish</th><th class="mono">G1 open</th><th class="mono">G2 open</th><th class="mono">G3 Pres. Cup</th><th class="mono">G4 Pan Am</th><th class="mono">G6 GP Series</th><th class="mono">G10 GP Final</th><th class="mono">G14 Worlds</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Gold</td><td class="mono">10</td><td class="mono">20</td><td class="mono">30</td><td class="mono">40</td><td class="mono">60</td><td class="mono">100</td><td class="mono big">140</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Silver</td><td class="mono">6</td><td class="mono">12</td><td class="mono">18</td><td class="mono">24</td><td class="mono">36</td><td class="mono">60</td><td class="mono">84</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Bronze</td><td class="mono">3.6</td><td class="mono">7.2</td><td class="mono">10.8</td><td class="mono">14.4</td><td class="mono">21.6</td><td class="mono">36</td><td class="mono">50.4</td></tr>
        <tr><td>5th</td><td class="mono">2.16</td><td class="mono">4.32</td><td class="mono">6.48</td><td class="mono">8.64</td><td class="mono">12.96</td><td class="mono">15.12</td><td class="mono">30.24</td></tr>
        <tr><td>9th</td><td class="mono">1.51</td><td class="mono">3.02</td><td class="mono">4.54</td><td class="mono">6.05</td><td class="mono">9.07</td><td class="mono">10.58</td><td class="mono">21.17</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table></div>
    <p class="small">GP Challenge uses the G2 column (and pays its 4th place 4.32). Olympic Games (G20) gold is 200 — beyond this campaign's scope.</p>

    <div class="callout red"><div class="k">The cap — the rule most people miss</div>All <strong>G1 + G2 + G3</strong> results combined can contribute a <strong>maximum of 40 points across all of 2027</strong> (plus 20 in Jan–May 2028, which lands after the deadline). Two good G2 wins and that bucket is full. <strong>One GP Series gold (60) beats a whole year of opens.</strong> Small events are for cracking into the ranking early — not for the final total.</div>

    <div class="callout blue"><div class="k">Two events that dodge the cap</div><strong>Pan Am President's Cup</strong> (own-continent G3, gold 30) and the <strong>GP Challenge</strong> (G2, gold 20) are explicitly <em>excluded</em> from the 40-point cap. Stacked with the capped 40, that's up to 90 points from "minor" events.</div>

    <div class="grid g3">
      <div class="card"><div class="k" style="color:var(--chung)">Cumulation</div><p class="small">The −68kg Olympic ranking sums points from <strong>three</strong> World divisions: −63, −68 and −74. Points won at −63 count toward −68 (see §10).</p></div>
      <div class="card"><div class="k" style="color:var(--chung)">No decay in 2027</div><p class="small">Everything won in 2027 sits at <strong>full value</strong> in the Jan 2028 ranking. Pack the calendar — there's no penalty for volume.</p></div>
